E. Create a user defined function in python to check the outliers using IQR method. Then pass all numeric variables in that function to check outliers

In[84]:
def detect_outliers_iqr(dataframe, column):
    q1 = dataframe[column].quantile(0.25)
    q3 = dataframe[column].quantile(0.75)
    iqr = q3 - q1
    lower_bound = q1 - 1.5 * iqr
    upper_bound = q3 + 1.5 * iqr
    outliers = dataframe[(dataframe[column] < lower_bound) | (dataframe[column] > upper_bound)][column]
    return { "Lower Bound": lower_bound,
        "Upper Bound": upper_bound,
        "Outliers": outliers.tolist()}
outlier_results = {}
for column in num_variables.columns:
    outlier_results[column] = detect_outliers_iqr(num_variables, column)
for col, result in outlier_results.items():
    print(f"Column: {col}")
    print(f"Lower Bound: {result['Lower Bound']}")
    print(f"Upper Bound: {result['Upper Bound']}")
    print(f"Number of Outliers: {len(result['Outliers'])}")
    print(f"Outliers: {result['Outliers'][:5]}")
    print("-" * 50)

Q2. Explain Gradient descent in detail. How changing the values of learning rate can impact the convergence in Gradient Descent.

Gradient Descent- It is a process which is used in Machine learning to reduce the loss. we will take an intial value and than we will iterate it until it reaches the point where x=0 and it is called Global Minima. first my model will calculate the slope which is delta of loss divided by delta of weight where weight is hyperparameter and it will iterate till the point of global minima and this is the point where we will be having the minimum loss.

Changing the values of Learning rate- General consideration for learning rate is 0.3 and if we will reduce the learning rate we will still get the result but Epoch will increase which means it will take more iteration due to this it take more time and If we will increase the learning rate it will keep jumping from one point to another and will become a loop but will never reach the global minima.
